<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1733" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1733">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 823.124/42.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 1, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to enclose herewith, for
                            transmission to the President of Peru, the letter of acceptance of Mr.
                            Bayless.</p>
                        <p>Mr. Bayless informs the Department that a Mr. Keegan, one of the
                            assistants in the Health Department of the city of Richmond, Virginia,
                            has agreed to join him at Iquitos, sailing on November 15, and Mr.
                            Keegan’s letter of acceptance will be forwarded later.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>